"On average, a total of about 1,200 internal security breaches occur in UK businesses every single day. In the US, the figure is over 2,500. These figures are based on recent research in which 500 IT decision makers were asked whether they had had an internal security breach in the past year. 1 Yet despite this huge prolificacy, they also said that insider threats are not top of their list of security priorities. In fact they come a fairly distant fourth, after viruses, data loss and hacking. On average, a total of about 1,200 internal security breaches occur in UK businesses every single day. In the US, the figure is over 2,500. Yet despite this, insider threats are not among organisations' top security priorities. For IT managers, internal security is a lesser priority than data loss, despite the fact that the most common source of data loss is via employees. Why is that? Francois Amigorena of IS Decisions explains how the insider threat needs to be addressed with a combination of cultural and technological solutions."
